main event: A civilian observed a metallic, disc-shaped object in Mesquita, Texas on June 11, 1966.
interesting points: The sighting lasted approximately 10 minutes and was observed by at least four witnesses., The object was larger than a passenger jet and displayed an oscillating motion., The object appeared and disappeared from view during the observation., The object's movements suggested it was intelligently controlled and much faster than conventional aircraft., A letter from Project Blue Book indicated insufficient data for evaluation despite the detailed sighting report.
